    "chemicalDescription": [
      "s-Cannabis Sativa Nonapeptide-1 is a single chain peptide consisting of alanine, arginine, glycine, leucine, proline, serine, threonine, tryptophan and valine. It is synthetically produced based on a sequence from Edestin 1 which is found in Cannabis sativa. The parent protein contains a maximum of 511 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation."
